UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 415
1 AN ACT relating to the issuance of identity documents.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 186 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Local governmental entity" means a:
7 1. Public library as defined in KRS 171.125; or
8 2. City; and
9 (b) "Local official" means a circuit clerk, county clerk, county sheriff, or
10 county judge/executive.
11 (2) The Transportation Cabinet shall expand the availability of driver licensing
12 services by establishing a system in which one (1) local official or local
13 governmental entity in each county may issue operator's licenses and personal
14 identification cards through a mutual agreement between that local official or
15 local governmental entity and the Transportation Cabinet. The Transportation
16 Cabinet shall identify a local official or local governmental entity in each county
17 to participate in the system by July 1, 2027.
18 (3) The Transportation Cabinet shall purchase and install all necessary equipment
19 and hardware for each local official or local governmental entity issuing
20 operator's licenses and personal identification cards under this section.
21 (4) In addition to the fees set forth in Section 2 of this Act, a local official or local
22 governmental entity may charge and retain a convenience fee for each operator's
23 license or personal identification card issued under this section.
24 (5) A local official or local governmental entity issuing documents under this section
25 shall not issue commercial driver's licenses or travel IDs.
26 (6) By October 1, 2028, and annually thereafter, the Transportation Cabinet shall
27 report to the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint
