UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 415
1 Committee on Transportation on:
2 (a) The number of operator's licenses and personal identification cards issued
3 in each county during the previous fiscal year under this section; and
4 (b) Information regarding the effect that issuance of identity documents by
5 local officials and local governmental entities had on wait times at regional
6 licensing offices.
7 Section 2. KRS 186.531 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) As used in this section:
9 (a) "GF" means the general fund;
10 (b) "IP" means instruction permit;
11 (c) "License fund" or "LF" means the KYTC photo license account created in
12 KRS 174.056;
13 (d) "MC" means motorcycle;
14 (e) "MC fund" or "MCF" means the motorcycle safety education program fund
15 established in KRS 176.5065;
16 (f) "OL" means operator's license; and
17 (g) "PIDC" means personal identification card.
18 (2) The fees imposed for voluntary travel ID operator's licenses, instruction permits,
19 and personal identification cards shall be as follows. The fees received shall be
20 distributed as shown in the table. The fees shown, unless otherwise noted, are for an
21 eight (8) year period:
22 Card Type Fee LF GF MCF
23 OL (initial/renewal) $48 $48 $0 $0
24 OL (Under 21) (Up to 4 years) $18 $18 $0 $0
25 Any OL, MC, or combination
26 (duplicate/corrected) $15 $13.25 $1.75 $0
27 Motor vehicle IP (3 years) $18 $16 $2 $0
